POLICE watchdogs investigating the death in custody of Sheku Bayoh are keen to speak to the drivers of nine vehicles.
The appeal follows extensive examination of CCTV footage taken in the area of Hayfield Road and Hendry Road, in Kirkcaldy, on the morning Sheku died.
The Police Investigations and Review Commissioner want to speak to the drivers who were seen in the area between 7.10am and 7.25am on Sunday 3 May.

The vehicles involved are-
Investigators have stressed that any sighting is relevant to the enquiry. Any person recognising their own vehicle, or the vehicle of someone they know from the CCTV images or footage, should contact them on 01698 544291 .
